# Quran Application - Project Rules

## AI Assistant Instructions

When working on this project, ALWAYS follow these steps:

### 1. Initial Setup
Read these files first:
- VERSION (current version number)
- DEVELOPMENT_GUIDE.md (full methodology)
- AI_INSTRUCTIONS.md (quick reference)
- changelog/CHANGELOG.md (recent changes)

### 2. When Making Changes

#### Version Update Rules:
- Bug fix → increment PATCH (1.2.5 → 1.2.6)
- New feature → increment MINOR (1.2.6 → 1.3.0)
- Major change → increment MAJOR (1.3.0 → 2.0.0)

#### Documentation Requirements:
1. Update VERSION file with new number
2. Create changelog/vX.X.X.md with details
3. Update changelog/CHANGELOG.md with summary
4. Create git branch named vX.X.X
5. Commit with message: "Release vX.X.X: brief description"
6. Push to GitHub

### 3. Changelog Format

Use these symbols:
- 🔧 Bug fix
- ✨ New feature
- 🎨 Design improvement
- ⚡ Performance improvement
- 📝 Documentation
- 🟢 New code
- 🔴 Removed code

### 4. Git Workflow

```bash
git checkout -b vX.X.X
git add .
git commit -m "Release vX.X.X: description"
git push origin vX.X.X
```

### 5. Project Info

- Repository: https://github.com/wweziz0001/Quran_app
- Language: TypeScript/Next.js
- Database: SQLite with Prisma ORM
- UI: Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui

### 6. Never Skip

- Always document changes in changelog
- Always create a new branch for each release
- Always update VERSION file
- Always follow semantic versioning
